  "body": "### Describe the bug\r\n\r\nAt the moment the `quarkus deploy kubernetes` command is not meant to trigger a build unless requested using the `--image-build` property.\r\n\r\nHowever, this does not seem to be the case when a container image extension is already available in the project, in which cases its just used.\r\n\r\n### How to Reproduce?\r\n\r\n```sh\r\nquarkus create app reproducer -x quarkus-container-image-jib\r\ncd reprodcuer\r\nquarkus kubernetes deploy\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Findings\r\nIt seems the kubernetes deployer requests an image push as a pre-requisitive of the deploy action, unless its explicitly disabled. The CLI does disable the build by default, but not the push. As a result when a container image extension is present in the project a push is attempted.\r\n\r\n\r\n### Implementation ideas\r\n\r\n- We should never implicitly push when build is explicitly disabled.\r\n\r\n",
